AIMING TRAINING

CS Single-Player

Map Info ---------- - Map Version: V1.0 - Working Progress: 1 day - simple dev textures - 10 enemys to kill - unlimited ammo, money and health - improved lighting - collect XP in-game and in your brain - learn how to kill in distances quickly - map designed for SINGLE-PLAYER game - join only as CT and let join 10 bots to T - bot-quota set to 10 - you get 50% transparency This map was designed for Single-Player. sv-cheats 1 is enabled on this map, because the map need bot-stop 1. You have to join Counter Terrorist >**ONLY**. Health, Ammo and Money are unlimited. The mission is to kill all 10 Targets. While you kill them you gain XP (1550 XP Max.). Please do not change any values in console! All entities in the map will do the work, you only have to kill the bots. Be sure you have tick Bot join after player before you starting Created Server. You can only use all CT weapons without AK 47, Dual Elites, Krieg 552, D3/AU-1 and IDF Defender. I found the answer... you need only to write in console at start give and behind it weapon ID. The list is below. - give weapon_ak47 //gives AK-47 - give weapon_elite //gives Dual Elites - give weapon_sg552 //gives Krieg 552 (Zooming Rifle) - give weapon_g3sg1 //gives D3/AU-1 (Auto-Sniper) - give weapon_galil //gives IDF Defender (Galil) If you want to get full Money and Ammo, you need to write in console sv_cheats 1 and after that impulse 101. The impulse 101 command is only available on activate cheats, so not really for multiplayer. - impulse 101 //reset all Money and Ammo to full capacity Special Thanks -------------- - TopHATTWaffle - Dev Textures Bug Reports ----------- Please report all bugs on GameBanana Comments page. Changelog --------- To watch all changes pls watch in Updates section. _____________________________________________________________________________

Please leave comments, rate, give feedback and subscribes if you like.
Enjoy!

Foreword : This map is NOT to be played without a certain Sourcemod plugin (or use another server modification; or simply try it and waste your time).

It works under BOTH CSS and CSGO (the b01 version didn't work for CSGO).

This map is close replicate to cs_deagle5. However, a full "board" of boxes are between T and CT spawn. There are NO path (nor bridge). 

Using a certain plugin (see below's link), you'll be able to produce a different maze every X rounds (which is the point of the project).

The map was done through December2012 and January2013 (I just never found time to release both map+plugin).

Original plugin's thread : [https://forums.alliedmods.net/showthread.php?t=220159](https://forums.alliedmods.net/showthread.php?t=220159 "Red Maze (of Red Wonders)")

This is basically a really fun map in which you can improve your aim and CQB skills. It's a dark world so you got to use your flashlight. You'll be able to use any weapon since I've included a buyzone.
I would say it's kinda simple in many aspects, but I personally find it quite entertaining at same time; and hopefully you will get hooked for many hours, too!

In fact, I firstly got this map from the following link:

_http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/132702_

I modified it and made a lot of changes so I could have fun with an alternative and more complex version. Just felt like sharing it with you guys (girls or w/e).

[Video (preview)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=npKFfj8J_ok "Video (preview)")

Hello there! so this one basically consists on a C.Q.B. training facility, which implements multiple rooms with targets and Flashbangs on the floor (so you can actually make more tactical entries). I suggest you to watch the preview video, in order to find out how you should specifically proceed with the clearing thingy, so you can have more fun and avoid getting lost since it's a bit complicated map. You may find some civilians, so watch out with your aim.
Don't try joining miserable T's team or you will regret, since there's only one spawn point for them (located inside an underwater cell) and you will constantly die by either laser blasts or drown (don't ask me why I did this).
There's Buy Zone option in the whole map so you can use the weapons you want wherever you are, although I highly recommend to use the ones of the metallic tables (UMP-45, Sig Sauer P-228, AWP and M3), since they have all the ammo you will need.
You may consider allowing flashlight or equipping Night Vision Goggles because of some dark sites.

In fact, this map did firstly belong to some user known as Starving Hobo. I completely modified it to have more fun with an alternative and complex version; and just felt sharing with you guys (or girls w/e).

[Starving Hobo version (original)](http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/132702 "")

Also, some prefabs like the guard tower, helicopter and cabins (which are located outside) are not mine.
Can't remember author names, though. I'm sorry about that.

I finally want to say that I've spent sooo much time to make this compilation, trying to find interesting things to add to the map, texturing, creating walls, the skybox (the ones I created always gave me error so I had to take it from another map, and delete step by step in order to use it's skybox) and shit.
So it's made with love, and hopefully you'll enjoy this probably simple but sweet piece of art too.

*INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

Simply place the Maps and Materials (helicopter texture) folders into your Cstrike one and you're done.

Hello again, Gamebanana!
So today I'm releasing a quite improved version of my last map (CQB_Training). For the ones who don't know about it, this map basically consists on a facility which implements several rooms with targets. There's a Buyzone so in fact you can use the weapons you want, although I highly recommend taking the ones from the table; since they got all the ammo you'll need (there's MP5, USP, Scout and XM1014). I've included the .VMF file so feel free to make changes.

In this new version I've added multiple characters around the map with different positions (sit, crossed arms... etc) which stands for an impressive decorative element from my point of view. I highly recommend downloading CT_hostages (http://gamebanana.com/css/skins/12054) in order to make those characters appear as Urban. Also, as the titles states the route is extended, so you'll have to do a few more things (like assaulting a little train and 2 warehouses). These prefabs plus the guard tower were not made by me by the way.

Well, that's all. And don't forget to watch the specific video if you haven't watched it yet; the ideal thing would be to act more or less like I did. Enjoy ;D

[Map preview (click me!)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JBI6CQm1eqk "Map preview")

Hello there! during all this time I've been playing on my beloved "CS:S Training Center" map, but I got bored so I made a new one. The thing is that this time is made completely by me; without using a base that already exists.

One more time, the map consists on a training facility in which you will be able to have fun by testing your aiming skills through an specific route. The map basically implements several rooms with targets, and a long shooting range (this one is so boring to me that I didn't take care about placing a sniper rifle or showing it in the video).
I also didn't place flashbangs on the floor for the entries, unlike I did in my last map (this is because I sadly suffered from very slow frame rate).
There's a Buyzone so in fact you can use the weapons you want, although I highly recomment using the ones that are on the table (M4A1 and Sig Sauer P-228) since they got all the ammo you will need.

I have included the VMF. file so you can modify whatever you want (like the weapons for example).

So that's all folks; I hope you enjoy it as much as I did atleast and I'm sorry if wall of text.

*UPDATE! :

Added some HL2 guards around the map and AWP sniper rifle for the long shooting range
